parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, potentially leading to airbag deployment failure in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates intermittently
the airbag warning light remains on
the horn and cruise control stop working
the steering wheel controls fail
and the radio volume controls on the steering wheel fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and can also lead to traffic tickets for driving with defective equipment.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or go out intermittently
only one headlight works at a time
daytime running lights do not work
headlights work on low beam but not on high beam
or vice versa.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including headlight failure, instrument cluster light failure, and loss of power windows, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights and dashboard lights flicker or go out
power windows malfunction
instrument cluster lights fail
and other electrical components malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clockspring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and potentially prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
and the buttons on the steering wheel may not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Key does not turn in the ignition
and the vehicle may stall or fail to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights fail to work
or work intermittently
and may cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the body control module can cause various electrical malfunctions, including headlight failure, instrument cluster light failure, and loss of power windows, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Headlights and dashboard lights flicker or go out
power windows malfunction
instrument cluster lights fail
and other electrical components malfunction.
